<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Love of Learning</title>
  <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.0.0-alpha1/jquery.js"></script>
  
</head>
<body>
	<header>
		<data id="username" style="display: none;"><%= username %></data>
		<a href="/cbt">Home</a> | <a href="/users/<%= username %>/">User Dashboard</a> | 
		<a href="/users/<%= username %>/learning/show">Past Answers</a> | 
		<a href="/logout">Logout</a>
	</header>
	<section>
		<h1>Love of Learning</h1>
		<article>Most of us are born with some degree of curiousity about the world around us, but this quality can also be cultivated simply by investigating areas/ideas that are outside of our regular sphere or "comfort zone."</article>
	</section>

	<h2>Questions for <%= name %>:</h2>

	<form id="question-form" action="/users/<%= username %>/learning/create" method="post">

		<input type="hidden" name="username" value="<%= username %>">

		<div class="question">
		<h3 id="question-1">Name an idea or skill that I've added to my arsenal, or am working on adding. (e.g., starting to learn a language, working on my swimming stroke) </h3>
		<textarea form="question-form" id="question-1-textarea" name="answer1" cols="50" rows="10" placeholder="What have you been learning that you can add to your repertoire?"></textarea>
		<input type="hidden" name="question1" value="Name an idea or skill that I've added to my arsenal, or am working on adding. (e.g., starting to learn a language, working on my swimming stroke)?">
		</div>
		<div class="past-answers">
			<h4>Previous Answers</h4>
			<% rows.forEach(function (row) { %>
				<p><%= row.timestamp %>: <%= row.answer1 %></p>
			<% }) %>
		</div>
		<div class="question">
		<h3 id="question-2">What was the best book or article I read recently, and what was the main thing I learned from it?</h3>
		<textarea form="question-form" id="question-2-textarea" name="answer2" cols="50" rows="10" placeholder="What have you learned from a recent book or article?"></textarea>
		<input type="hidden" name="question2" value="What was the best book or article I read recently, and what was the main thing I learned from it?">
		</div>
		<div class="past-answers">
			<h4>Previous Answers</h4>
			<% rows.forEach(function (row) { %>
				<p><%= row.timestamp %>: <%= row.answer2 %></p>
			<% }) %>
		</div>
		
		<div class="question">
		<h3 id="question-3">What was the best movie I saw recently, and what was the main thing I got out of it?</h3>
		<textarea form="question-form" id="question-3-textarea" name="answer3" cols="50" rows="10" placeholder="Seen anything good lately? What did you learn?"></textarea>
		<input type="hidden" name="question3" value="What was the best movie I saw recently, and what was the main thing I got out of it?">
		</div>
		<div class="past-answers">
			<h4>Previous Answers</h4>
			<% rows.forEach(function (row) { %>
				<p><%= row.timestamp %>: <%= row.answer3 %></p>
			<% }) %>
		</div>
		<div class="question">
			<h3>For any random or stray thought about the topic that was not addressed by one of the prompts</h3>
			<textarea name="random_thought" id="random-textarea" cols="50" rows="10" placeholder="The perfect place for a random thought!"></textarea>
		</div>
		<div class="past-answers" id="random-answer">
			<h4>Previous Answers</h4>
			<% rows.forEach(function (row) { %>
				<% if (!row.random) { %>
					<% console.log('nothing'); %>
					<% } else { %>
				<p><%= row.timestamp %>: <%= row.random %></p>
				<% } %>
			<% }) %>
		</div>
		<br>
		<input id="learning-submit-button" type="submit" value="Submit Answers">

	</form>
	<script src="/javascript/learning.js"></script>
</body>
</html>